e, and a selection of works by Bill Viola, Lawrence Malstaf, Victoria Reynolds, and Berlinde de Bruyckere—all of whom, in their respective ways and media, recycle religious motifs and iconography and whose works resonate with, or problematize the motif of, the true image.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aArt and religion. 0aArt, Moderny20th centuryxThemes, motives. 0aArt, Moderny21st centuryxThemes, motives. 0aIdols and images in art. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh  aacheiropoietos.  aappropriation.  acontemporary art.  acounter-motif.  acult image.  aeras of the image.  aexhibition.  aiconoclasm.  ainstallation.  apainting.  apresentation.  aready-made.  aregimes of the image.  areligious iconography.  areligious motif.  asculpture.  aspirituality.  avideo-art.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082327450540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823274505423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823274505.jpg  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK